  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 512a72de08c75cf4e8a8424f7b75a271, type: 3}
  m_Name: D3T8_LadyTalkAfterPoker_Dialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  npc: 36
  sequence:
  - dialogueText: I saw you at the poker table. From your face, I'm guessing it didn't
      go well.
    buttonText: Total disaster
  - dialogueText: Can't blame me, I warned you. The Boss sounded like he was about
      to have a heart attack from up here.
    buttonText: He could've
  - dialogueText: Anyway, did you talk to the guy on the balcony?
    buttonText: Yeah
  - dialogueText: And? What did he have to say about why nobody can leave?
    buttonText: Said he didn't know
  - dialogueText: Really? You actually believed that? I've been watching him for
      a while... I'm pretty sure he's hiding something.
    buttonText: Why?
  - dialogueText: He's always watching. You don't stay that quiet unless you know
      what's going on. Did you ask him about your bottle?
    buttonText: I tried
  - dialogueText: And he wouldn't talk about that either?
    buttonText: Yep
  - dialogueText: We really need to figure this out. I'm tired of being stuck here.
    buttonText: Where to look?
  - dialogueText: I don't know yet. But he's definitely the one with the answers.
      He's just not talking.
    buttonText: I'll keep trying
  - dialogueText: You do that. And come back to see me if you find anything.
    buttonText: Will do
